# Active-root start and page fragments

Implicit `start`, const/runtime split and builder-owned assembly.

## Contract

- Input: active module-root top-level runtime statements and top-level const templates
- Output: an implicit `start()` header, runtime fragment strings and compile-time fragment metadata
- Decides: which active-root forms are runtime code, which fold into builder metadata and which imported-root bodies are suppressed
- Must not decide: HTML page assembly, route selection, backend lowering
- Invariant: HIR carries runtime code only and doesn't own document structure

## Main paths

- `src/compiler_frontend/headers/parse_file_headers.rs`
- `src/compiler_frontend/headers/types.rs`
- `src/compiler_frontend/ast/module_ast/finalization/`
- `src/projects/html_project/html_project_builder.rs`

